Myanmar Muslims Die as Evacuation Boat Capsizes
Several boats carrying more than 100 Rohingya Muslims from the path of an oncoming cyclone appeared to have capsized off the coast of western Myanmar, with only 42 people believed to have survived, the United Nations said Tuesday, as the incident revived worries about the country's planning for natural disasters.
The boats left a makeshift camp where the displaced Rohingyas lived in Pauktaw township in Myanmar's Rakhine state late Monday in search of a safer area before the rickety flotilla foundered after striking rocks off...